description: For sale: $419,900. Beautiful newer home featuring one level living with a walk-out lower level on a serene 4 acre lot with panoramic nature views. Inviting front porch to open floor plan with cozy gas fireplace in the living room, raised snack bar in the kitchen with custom cabinets, granite tops, glass tile back-splash, stainless steel appliances, walk-in pantry, and spacious informal dining area that leads to the large new deck. Wonderful laundry/mud room on the main floor leads to 3 car garage with trench drain, and RI for in floor heat. Master suite features a large walk-in closet, tall vanity with 2 sinks, separate tile shower and soaking tub. 2nd bedroom on main floor. Walk-out level features large family room with bar, 2 more bedrooms, and 3rd full bath. Walls insulated for sound, great storage, hot-water in floor heat, and forced air heat. You will enjoy the tranquility Spyder Lake  with beautiful trails, picnic areas and water access for canoes or kayaks.

description:
Recently sold: $399,000. Now ready to show, contact info updated.
Dream home for people that love outdoors!  200 feet of beautiful lake shore perfect for waterfowl hunting and fishing with a road to drive down in car or ride 4-wheeler to the lake or drive right out onto the ice for ice fishing.
Views also include a small fish pond, a beautiful willow tree down by the lake with mature flower beds and landscaping all over.
There is a porch/deck in front and out back as well as a cement patio for setting up outdoor furniture.
The lot is very secluded with trees and vegetation separating you from your neighbors.
A 3 stall pole barn with a custom made bar inside includes a giant lake view window and vaulted ceiling with fan. It's a dream for entertaining or relaxing between projects.
This rambler house is large with an attached 2 car garage. Currently is has 3 bedrooms, but it has had more in the past.
Walk out patio door from basement family room to cement patio and more flower gardens. Also there is a fenced in vegetable garden.
The living room has a nice fireplace with wood mantel and gorgeous wood bay window. It opens up into a big dining room with wall A/C and has a patio door that leads out onto the deck facing the lake.
The kitchen in the open area layout has a breakfast nook/center island and garden window over the sink with lake views.
To the left is a hallway that leads past a newly remodeled bathroom which includes a Jacuzzi tub and steam shower with a lake view window. This bathroom has another door to the master bedroom which has beautiful views of the lake and property.
The bedroom upstairs across from the bathroom is large enough for 2  people to share easily with 2 built in closets. It has two large windows facing the front yard which is like a park.
Entry way when you come in through the attached garage entrance has a beautiful sun room that overlooks the backyard and lake shore. It is large enough to create a relaxing reading area with small library.
After you go downstairs, there is a pantry and many storage shelves along a hallway that leads to two more rooms that could be used as bedrooms, storage or office space. One of the rooms needs an egress window to be listed as a fourth bedroom.
Then as you walk further into the basement, you pass the laundry room with a lake view window and second bathroom which includes a sit-down shower.
That opens up into a great room which can be used as a second family room, rec room, fitness center, or whatever you desire.
It currently has a 9 foot slate pool table and small bar in the largest part of it. The other half is still big enough to accommodate: a card table, treadmill, sofa, coffee table and entertainment hutch with TV.
This house is perfect for being able to enjoy the outdoors year round with ice skating, ice fishing, snowmobiling, sledding and cross country skiing options available in the winter.
The summer is great for campfires by the lake, boating, fishing off the dock or boat, exploring, hiking, gardening and relaxing outside taking in the beautiful views. 
The location is only 8 minutes North East of Forest Lake up highway 8 making it easily accessible to Interstate 35 and only a 30 minute drive to either St. Paul or Minneapolis. It is one hour north of MSP international airport. There are multiple places to shop, eat, activities, and all of your needs can be satisfied within a 10 - 15 minute drive including a top of the line hospital in Wyoming, MN.
The Chisago Lakes school district is rated very highly and the bus comes and picks up your children from the end of the driveway.
We are in the process of cleaning out 30 years of memories and plan to post more pictures ASAP. The pole barn is freshly painted and decks stained. We are having new rock put in driveway and installing new carpet.
Please call Ron Rotter (612) 232-9080 if you are interested in taking a look!

description:
Recently sold: $500,000. Chisago Lake Twp. is just 35 minutes to either downtown and close to main roads for ease of commuting. 

A former model home listed over $1m, this home has been enhanced with upgrades but does need a little TLC to shine. Resting on a 3.27 acres of woods including oaks, maples and pine trees. Wild strawberries, grapes and blackberries.
This gorgeous home, built in 2004 of concrete, is one of a kind with its rich detailing and quality craftsmanship. Elegant with a formal dining room for entertaining yet comfortable with cozy family and movie rooms, this home is perfect if you love space, quality or hosting a crowd. With concrete construction, you?ll find this home is very energy efficient and quiet.
Interior ? Main Floor: 
? Architectural features like tall, wide arches, wood and iron railings, perfectly maintained hardwood flooring, 10 foot or two story ceilings, deep tray ceilings?.ceiling fans?recessed lighting, slate tiles?
? A high two story foyer with hardwood flooring and a grand stairway greets you upon entering this home. Hardwood extends through to the Great Room, kitchen and informal dining area.
? A 16 x 14 room off the foyer is perfect for the main floor office or music room
? A grand 18 x 15 two story living/great room with large windows that allows an abundance of natural light and views of nature is warmed by a gas fireplace.
? A 25 x 14 Gourmet Kitchen that is perfect for entertaining or casual fun with breakfast bar and center island?double ovens, gas cooktop, beautiful granite countertops, slate backsplash and an abundance of maple cabinetry with pull out shelving, recycling bin and excellent storage; informal dining space. Lots of natural light with big windows.
? A 16 x 15 screened porch, right off the kitchen allows for outside dining for summer enjoyment
? Powder room with beautiful slate flooring and backsplash is convenient for guests or coming in from the garage.
? Double door entry to a 21 x 17 Main floor owners suite with high ceiling and deep tray vault, huge walk in closet and very spacious bath with gorgeous ceramic floor tiling and in the walk in shower (with multiple heads) 
Interior ? UPPER LEVEL
? Three large bedrooms and a bonus room
? Jack and Jill ceramic tiled bath
? Princess Suite or man cave?.with its own full bath
? Bonus room for upstairs 2nd office, study area or play room
? Excellent closet space and storage
Interior- Walkout Basement Level
? 19 x 16 movie room!
? 16 x 15 exercise room 
? Games are meant to be played in this family/game room space with a gas fireplace and large wet bar with a full refrigerator. Overnights are easy with the space in this basement?.
? Walkout to nature or enjoy from within with large windows allowing lots of natural light.
? Water softener and top of the line reverse osmosis system.
? Wine cellar, currently used as a storage room is located behind the bar.
? Exterior?
Well maintained stucco over concrete construction and vinyl siding makes this home very energy efficient. Low gas bills and extremely low noise inside allows for peaceful space throughout the home.
Spider Lake is a scenic lake meant for fishing or canoeing/kayaking. Saddle Shores is a quiet community with close proximity to Chisago City and Lindstrom with shopping and dining nearby and within 10 minutes of I-35. Only ten minutes to the St. Croix River Valley, a short drive to Taylors Falls and Still water and numerous terrific trails and camping parks.
Meant to be the nature environment close in, you can enjoy more nature time versus driving time! Directions I-35 No., Exit 132 toward Taylors Falls onto US-8, Right on Green Lk Trl (CR-23) Continue on Lofton Ave. (CR-24) Right on Chisago Blvd, Right on Morgan, Left on Maxwell

description: Recently sold: $350,000. This is a beautiful lake home on Chisago Lake, which is on a Chain of five lakes. Currently from Chisago Lake you can boat to two other lakes. One more bridge opening will open up to five lakes. In the 1930's this chain was one lake called Big Lake the plan is to return to one lake with 32 miles of shoreline . This is a full recreational lake.  From the dock you can catch Walleye, Northern pike, Bass, Pan fish, and Perch. This home has  150' of sandy lake shore with a large private lot 150x345x290x165, many mature trees. A over sized deck for entertaining and watching sunsets. The yard has been professionally landscaped, is fully fenced for pets or children . This home is a walk out rambler, on the main floor two bedrooms and a full bath, lower level one bedroom and a 3/4 bath, both floors have living space with large windows looking out to the lake. A wood burning fireplace for extra warmth on the lower level. A den off the upstairs living area.  This home is a easy forty minute drive to the twin cities and fifty minutes to the international airport. The snowmobile trail is on the lake in front of the house, which will get you any where in or out of the state, the trail system is excellent. This home has had many updates including a new roof, furnace , windows, doors, gutters and gutter guards, decks and retaining walls, drain tile, fascia and soffits, fencing, chimney, electric, custom blinds, quadra  Fire fireplace insert, paint, floors and more.

description: For sale: $439,900. Impressive 4 bedroom, 4 bath former model home. It's all about the view as you enter this home. Wall of windows in living room showcases expansive views and colorful sunsets. Enjoy the views inside by the cozy fireplace or out on the lovely new deck with pergola. Home has very desirable layout with kitchen open to dining and living room. Main floor also has a bedroom, 3/4 bath, laundry and mudroom with built-ins. Upstairs layout just as great. Master bedroom with vaulted ceiling, spa-like bath and walk-in closet. 2 additional bedrooms with Jack & Jill bathroom. Recently finished walkout lower level makes this home better than new! 1/2 bath, family room with wet bar, sink, refrigerator and dishwasher make it a great space for entertaining! Equipment has been removed in the salon room making it perfect for a 5th bedroom/workout room/office. Home is located near many lakes and other conveniences. Hurry to make this beautiful home yours!

Recently sold: $285,000. Enjoy a lovely, peaceful setting from this year round lake home on Lake Emily. Lake Emily is a weed less sand bottom lake with its own boat launch. Bring your boat and beach toys! 165' of frontage. This home offers so many updates including a great kitchen, main floor laundry, newer roof, siding, electrical, heating upgrades, septic system and 4 car garage. Great location! Street only 2 miles to two and an easy 10 minute drive to I-35 in Forest Lake.
